snippet.title: SEMA 2013
snippet.description: Custom cars and specialist auto products from the 2013 SEMA Show in Las Vegas.

snippet.title: Best tablets
snippet.description: CNET editors round up their favorite tablets, including products from Apple, Samsung, and Google.

snippet.title: Lenovo S850
snippet.description: Its specs are nothing special, but you're not going to miss the S850, a cheap new phone from the Chinese manufacturer.

snippet.title: Origin PC EON17-SLX
snippet.description: Cramming the most high-end parts into a massive 17-inch body will top $4,000, but you also get a powerful laptop that has more next-gen gaming muscle than any living-room console.

snippet.title: Flipboard for iOS
snippet.description: With tons of customization options and a unique magazine-style interface, anyone looking for a better way to browse the latest news and social info should definitely download this app immediately.

snippet.title: The Rolls-Royce of custom game controllers
snippet.description: High-end custom studio The Controller Shop gets credit for starting the personalized video game controller revolution.

snippet.title: Custom SLR Glide Strap
snippet.description: If you want something far superior to the bundled neck strap that came with your camera, the Custom SLR Glide Strap is a very comfortable alternative.

snippet.title: Olympus Stylus XZ-2 iHS
snippet.description: The Olympus Stylus XZ-2 iHS is an excellent bright lens enthusiast compact. At this point, though, you should skip it at its full $600 price.

snippet.title: Silk Road is resurrected with a new Dread Pirate Roberts
snippet.description: Deja vu? A new online drug marketplace appears as Silk Road 2.0 with an operator using the same pseudonym as the original site's alleged operator.

snippet.title: Linksys WRT1900AC Wireless Router
snippet.description: If you can afford the hefty price tag, the Linksys WRT1900AC Wi-Fi router is easily one of the best home routers on the market.
